T1  - Estimation The Level of Copeptin in Women With PCOS Pre and Post Metformin Treatment
A1  - Ahmied M.S.
A1  - Abood B.H.
A1  - Jabbar H.A.A.S. 
Y1  - 2018//
N2  - Polycystic ovary syndrome is a common endocrinopathies disorder that lead to metabolic and reproductive problem. To estimate the level of Copeptin in women with poly cystic ovary syndrome and to evaluate the effect of metformin treatment on the level of this hormone. Copeptin, testosterone by ELISA BMI by calculation in group of PCOS and control group before and after metformin treatment. The mean of plasma copeptin levels was significantly increase in patient with PCOS before treatment (p<0.05) compared with control group and the effect the metformin on level of copeptin also was significantly (p<0.05). The result of this study indicate the level of copeptin significantly incease in PCOS before and after metformin treatment so that the copeptin may be can used for early diagnosis CVD.Copyright © 2018. All Rights Reserved.
