160. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 633804108
T1  - Determinants of arterial stiffness in Alpha-1 Antitrypsin Deficiency
T3  - European Respiratory Society International Congress, ERS 2020. Virtual.
A1  - Gassama A.
A1  - Sapey L.
A1  - Griffiths D.
A1  - Stockley R.
A1  - Kumar P.
A1  - Turner A. 
Y1  - 2020//
N2  - Background: Cardiovascular disease (CVD) morbidity and mortality is high in patients with COPD. Smoking, environment and genetic factors such as Alpha-1 Antitrypsin Deficiency (AATD) are the major causes of emphysema. Arterial stiffness (AS) is a robust predictor of CVD in COPD. . We aimed to identify predictors of arterial stiffness in AATD cohort and assess interactions between systemic inflammation and hypoxia in modulating AS. Method(s): 181 Subjects (64% male) were recruited from the UK national registry for AATD. Pulse wave velocity (PWV) was used to measure AS. Pulmonary function tests, capillary blood gases were performed, and inflammatory markers measured from serum samples using ELISA. Result(s): Univariate analyses show PWV significantly correlated with age (r =0.655; p <=0.0001), sex (p <=0.010), TNF-alpha (r =0.178; p <=0.037), FEV1 %predicted (r =-0.174; p <=0.026), FEV1/FVC ratio (r=-0.240; p <=0.002), systolic pressure (r =0.433; p <=0.0001), pulse pressure (r =0.34; p <=0.0001), cardiac output (r =0.317; p <=0.0001), total peripheral resistance (r =-0.156; p <=0.043), TLCO (r =-0.366; p value <=0.0001), TLCO percent predicted (r =-0.315; p <=0.0001). Also, pO2 significantly correlated with all spirometry and gas transfer parameters as well as pulse pressure (r =0.224; p<=0.005) and aortic pulse pressure (r =0.214; p<=0.008). There was no significant correlation observed between PWV and IL-8, IL-1beta, pCO2 or pO2. Multivariate linear regression demonstrated that TNF-alpha, systolic pressure, FEV1, PO2 and TLCO together statistically predicted ~ 50% of variability in PWV. Conclusion(s): The findings suggest that TNF-alpha is associated with AS. We found no significant interaction between hypoxia and inflammation to modulate AS.
