T3  - 29th International Congress of the European Respiratory Society, ERS. Madrid Spain.
A1  - Han B.X.
A1  - Tian M.
A1  - Xu Y.
A1  - Wang Y.
A1  - Zhu L.
A1  - Han Y.
A1  - Chang Y.
A1  - Li J.
A1  - Ma J. 
Y1  - 2019//
N2  - Background: Benefits of AVAPS-AE(average volume assured pressure support auto-titrating EPAP) mode in AECOPD patient with heart failure(HF) has remained unclear. Objective(s): To assess efficacy of AVAPS-AE for AECOPD patients with HF and optimize the strategy for EPAP level. Method(s): A prospective, randomized, controlled and clinical trial,75 elderly(76+/-8.3yrs) AECOPD patients were included, who complicated with HF (NYHA>=II, NT-proBNP>=1800pg/ml)and had a history of coronary artery disease. All subjects were randomly divided into 3 groups(25 in each group): CPAP(continuous positive airway pressure) group, AVAPS group and AVAPS-AE group. Setting(s): EPAP=8cmH2O in CPAP group, EPAP=8cmH2O in AVAPS group, EPAP =4cmH2O and EPAPmax =14cmH2O in AVAPS-AE group, other parameters were similar. Result(s): Compared with CPAP and AVAPS group, there were greater reduction in area of lung CT infiltration and BNP level in AVAPS-AE group(p<0.001), significant improvement of Borg Score and HRQL(health-related quality of life) in AVAPS-AE group(p<0.01). The blood PCO2 and A-aDO2 decreased,PO2 increased significantly in AVAPS-AE group(p<0.05), other outcomes were recorded (Fig1). Conclusion(s): AVAPS-AE mode maybe lead to significant improvement in clinical outcomes of AECOPD with HF by supplying with auto-titrating EPAP, the adaptive strategy for EPAP should be a varying and dynamic scale rather than a fixed parameter, during NIV. (Figure Presented) .
